# Team SDD memory

Before work: read root README, your component README, and `openspec/specs/<domain>/spec.md`. Product shapes live in `spec.md`.

## Hard rules
- No cross-edit: only your folder/branch; talk contracts, never neighbors' files.
- Contract discipline: additive-only mid-sprint; consumers ignore unknown fields.
- Only `orchestration/` imports other components.
- TDD: write or update failing tests before implementation for behavior changes.
- SDD review: OpenSpec + README stay SoT; finish with a review pass.
- Subagents: Cursor Grok 4.5 for task implementation and review.

## Git (auto commit + push)
- After each logical unit of work on your feature branch (tests green for that slice): auto-commit with a concise why-focused message — do not wait to be asked.
- Immediately after each commit: `git push -u origin HEAD` (auto-push; do not batch).
- Stage only owned/relevant files; never commit secrets (`.env`, keys, API tokens).
- Never force-push `main`/`master`. No `--no-verify` unless the owner explicitly asks.
- Merge conflicts: rebase or merge your branch; resolve only files you own; keep contracts additive-only; re-run your tests; commit the resolution; push. Do not "win" by editing a teammate's folder — escalate the contract instead.

## Evolution protocol
Update this rule only after reviewed work lands. Add a Learned bullet only for a durable, verified, team-wide convention. Cite source+date; replace stale; no secrets/guesses; max 10 learned bullets; the edit MUST appear in the task diff.

